<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Load2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Load,</orth> vb. (impf. not used; partic. <cit><quote>laden:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1022" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1022</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.11.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 11, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.123" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 123</bibl>. <cit><quote>loaden:</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 37</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 1, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.164" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 3, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.5.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 5, 50</bibl>) 1) to freight, to burden, to encumber: <cit><quote>like --en branches,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 2</bibl></cit> (F<hi rend="sub">2. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 2</bibl> 4</hi> <emph>--ed</emph>). <cit><quote>to l. a falling man,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.3.77" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 77</bibl></cit>. Followed by <cit><quote>with:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1022" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1022</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 1, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.5.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 5, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.11.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 11, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.123" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 123</bibl>.<lb />2) to furnish or provide in abundance, to adorn, to reward: <cit><quote>to l. thy merit richly,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.5.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 5, 74</bibl></cit>. Followed by <emph>with</emph>: <cit><quote>to l. my she with knacks,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.360" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 360</bibl></cit>. <emph>to l. him with his desert</emph> (with what he deserves) <bibl n="shak. h5 3.7.85" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 7, 85</bibl>. <cit><quote>preferments, with which the time will l. him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 1, 37</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to l. me with precepts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 4.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 1, 9</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with honour,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.164" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 164</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.6.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 6, 18</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>